<doc id="1091944" wikidata="Q4842919" url="?curid=1091944" title="Bahujan Samaj Party of Nepal">
<text>Bahujan Samaj Party, Nepal (Majority Society Party, Nepal) is a Nepalese political party. It is inspired by the Kanshi Ram&#x27;s Bahujan Samaj Party of India and led by Madan Bahadur Pradhan. In the 1999 general elections it had 3 candidates. The party got 0.01% of the votes nationwide. Right now its national president is Ganga Prasad Mahara.

