<doc id="1092155" wikidata="Q2963206" url="?curid=1092155" title="Chhatrapati">
<text>Chhatrapati is a royal title from Sanskrit used to denote a king. The word &quot;Chhatrapati&quot; is a Sanskrit language compound word of &quot;chhatra&quot; (&quot;parasol&quot; or &quot;umbrella&quot;) and &quot;pati&quot; (&quot;master/lord/ruler&quot;).

