Looking at the first term of this result, when formula_13 the negative frequency formula_14 cancels the positive frequency, leaving just the constant coefficient formula_15 (because formula_16), which causes the infinite integral to diverge. At other values of formula_3 the residual oscillations cause the integral to converge to zero. This &quot;idealized&quot; Fourier transform is usually written as:

